message.content: One of the most significant events that occurred in South Africa in the past 20 years was the death of Nelson Mandela, the country's first black president and iconic anti-apartheid leader, on December 5, 2013. Mandela's death marked the end of an era and had a profound impact on the nation and the world. His leadership and struggle against apartheid played a pivotal role in South Africa's transition from a racially divided society to a democracy. Mandela's legacy continues to inspire and shape the country to this day.
